    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1886-12-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1886-12-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="138" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d138">
                <head>No. 138.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Denby</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1886-12-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 18, 1886</date>.
                            (Received February 12, 1887.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 273.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform the Department of
                        the appointment of Marquis Tseng, late Chinese minister to England and
                        Russia, as minister of the Tsung-li yamên. I will only say that his
                        appointment is regarded as a good one.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Denby.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
